56// TODO For backward compatibility, in future versions we should remove this (extensions are preferred)
57const char* SkinTheme::kThemesFolderName = "themes";
58
59// This class offer backward compatibility with old themes, completing
60// or changing styles from the default theme to match the default
61// theme of previous versions, so third-party themes can look like
62// they are running in the old Aseprite without any modification.
63struct app::skin::SkinTheme::BackwardCompatibility {
64 bool hasSliderStyle = false;
65 void notifyStyleExistence(const char* styleId) {
66 if (std::strcmp(styleId, "slider") == 0)
67 hasSliderStyle = true;
68 }
69 void createMissingStyles(SkinTheme* theme) {
70 if (!hasSliderStyle &&
71 theme->styles.slider() &&
72 theme->styles.miniSlider()) {
73 // Old slider style
74 ui::Style style(nullptr);
75 os::Font* font = theme->getDefaultFont();
76 const int h = font->height();
77
78 style.setId(theme->styles.slider()->id());
79 style.setFont(font);
80
81 auto part = theme->parts.sliderEmpty();
82 style.setBorder(
83 gfx::Border(part->bitmapW()->width()-1*guiscale(),
84 part->bitmapN()->height()+h/2,
85 part->bitmapE()->width()-1*guiscale(),
86 part->bitmapS()->height()-1*guiscale()+h/2));
87
88 *theme->styles.slider() = style;
89 *theme->styles.miniSlider() = style;
90 }
91 }
92};

115static FontData* load_font(std::map<std::string, FontData*>& fonts,
116 const TiXmlElement* xmlFont,
117 const std::string& xmlFilename)
118{
119 const char* fontRef = xmlFont->Attribute("font");
120 if (fontRef) {
121 auto it = fonts.find(fontRef);
122 if (it == fonts.end())
123 throw base::Exception("Font named '%s' not found\n", fontRef);
124 return it->second;
125 }
126
127 const char* nameStr = xmlFont->Attribute("name");
128 if (!nameStr)
129 throw base::Exception("No \"name\" or \"font\" attributes specified on <font>");
130
131 std::string name(nameStr);
132
133 // Use cached font data
134 auto it = fonts.find(name);
135 if (it != fonts.end())
136 return it->second;
137
138 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Loading font '%s'\n", name.c_str());
139
140 const char* typeStr = xmlFont->Attribute("type");
141 if (!typeStr)
142 throw base::Exception("<font> without 'type' attribute in '%s'\n",
143 xmlFilename.c_str());
144
145 std::string type(typeStr);
146 std::string xmlDir(base::get_file_path(xmlFilename));
147 std::unique_ptr<FontData> font(nullptr);
148
149 if (type == "spritesheet") {
150 const char* fileStr = xmlFont->Attribute("file");
151 if (fileStr) {
152 font.reset(new FontData(os::FontType::SpriteSheet));
153 font->setFilename(base::join_path(xmlDir, fileStr));
154 }
155 }
156 else if (type == "truetype") {
157 const char* platformFileAttrName =
158#ifdef _WIN32
159 "file_win"
160#elif defined __APPLE__
161 "file_mac"
162#else
163 "file_linux"
164#endif
165 ;
166
167 const char* platformFileStr = xmlFont->Attribute(platformFileAttrName);
168 const char* fileStr = xmlFont->Attribute("file");
169 bool antialias = true;
170 if (xmlFont->Attribute("antialias"))
171 antialias = bool_attr_is_true(xmlFont, "antialias");
172
173 std::string fontFilename;
174 if (platformFileStr)
175 fontFilename = app::find_font(xmlDir, platformFileStr);
176 if (fileStr && fontFilename.empty())
177 fontFilename = app::find_font(xmlDir, fileStr);
178
179 // The filename can be empty if the font was not found, anyway we
180 // want to keep the font information (e.g. to use the fallback
181 // information of this font).
182 font.reset(new FontData(os::FontType::FreeType));
183 font->setFilename(fontFilename);
184 font->setAntialias(antialias);
185
186 if (!fontFilename.empty())
187 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Font file '%s' found\n", fontFilename.c_str());
188 }
189 else {
190 throw base::Exception("Invalid type=\"%s\" in '%s' for <font name=\"%s\" ...>\n",
191 type.c_str(), xmlFilename.c_str(), name.c_str());
192 }
193
194 FontData* result = nullptr;
195 if (font) {
196 fonts[name] = result = font.get();
197 font.release();
198
199 // Fallback font
200 const TiXmlElement* xmlFallback =
201 (const TiXmlElement*)xmlFont->FirstChild("fallback");
202 if (xmlFallback) {
203 FontData* fallback = load_font(fonts, xmlFallback, xmlFilename);
204 if (fallback) {
205 int size = 10;
206 const char* sizeStr = xmlFont->Attribute("size");
207 if (sizeStr)
208 size = std::strtol(sizeStr, nullptr, 10);
209
210 result->setFallback(fallback, size);
211 }
212 }
213 }
214 return result;
215}

232
233SkinTheme::~SkinTheme()
234{
235 // Delete all cursors.
236 for (auto& it : m_cursors)
237 delete it.second; // Delete cursor
238
239 if (m_sheet)
240 m_sheet->dispose();
241
242 m_parts_by_id.clear();
243
244 // Destroy fonts
245 for (auto& kv : m_fonts)
246 delete kv.second; // Delete all FontDatas
247 m_fonts.clear();
248}

283void SkinTheme::loadFontData()
284{
285 LOG("THEME: Loading fonts\n");
286
287 std::string fonstFilename("fonts/fonts.xml");
288
289 ResourceFinder rf;
290 rf.includeDataDir(fonstFilename.c_str());
291 if (!rf.findFirst())
292 throw base::Exception("File %s not found", fonstFilename.c_str());
293
294 XmlDocumentRef doc = open_xml(rf.filename());
295 TiXmlHandle handle(doc.get());
296
297 TiXmlElement* xmlFont = handle
298 .FirstChild("fonts")
299 .FirstChild("font").ToElement();
300 while (xmlFont) {
301 load_font(m_fonts, xmlFont, rf.filename());
302 xmlFont = xmlFont->NextSiblingElement();
303 }

357void SkinTheme::loadXml(BackwardCompatibility* backward)
358{
359 const int scale = guiscale();
360
361 // Load the skin XML
362 std::string xml_filename(base::join_path(m_path, "theme.xml"));
363
364 XmlDocumentRef doc = open_xml(xml_filename);
365 TiXmlHandle handle(doc.get());
366
367 // Load Preferred scaling
368 m_preferredScreenScaling = -1;
369 m_preferredUIScaling = -1;
370 {
371 TiXmlElement* xmlTheme = handle
372 .FirstChild("theme").ToElement();
373 if (xmlTheme) {
374 const char* screenScaling = xmlTheme->Attribute("screenscaling");
375 const char* uiScaling = xmlTheme->Attribute("uiscaling");
376 if (screenScaling)
377 m_preferredScreenScaling = std::strtol(screenScaling, nullptr, 10);
378 if (uiScaling)
379 m_preferredUIScaling = std::strtol(uiScaling, nullptr, 10);
380 }
381 }
382
383 // Load fonts
384 {
385 TiXmlElement* xmlFont = handle
386 .FirstChild("theme")
387 .FirstChild("fonts")
388 .FirstChild("font").ToElement();
389 while (xmlFont) {
390 const char* idStr = xmlFont->Attribute("id");
391 FontData* fontData = load_font(m_fonts, xmlFont, xml_filename);
392 if (idStr && fontData) {
393 std::string id(idStr);
394 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Loading theme font %s\n", idStr);
395
396 int size = 10;
397 const char* sizeStr = xmlFont->Attribute("size");
398 if (sizeStr)
399 size = std::strtol(sizeStr, nullptr, 10);
400
401 os::Font* font = fontData->getFont(size);
402 m_themeFonts[idStr] = font;
403
404 if (id == "default")
405 m_defaultFont = font;
406 else if (id == "mini")
407 m_miniFont = font;
408 }
409
410 xmlFont = xmlFont->NextSiblingElement();
411 }
412 }
413
414 // No available font to run the program
415 if (!m_defaultFont)
416 throw base::Exception("There is no default font");
417 if (!m_miniFont)
418 m_miniFont = m_defaultFont;
419
420 // Load dimension
421 {
422 TiXmlElement* xmlDim = handle
423 .FirstChild("theme")
424 .FirstChild("dimensions")
425 .FirstChild("dim").ToElement();
426 while (xmlDim) {
427 std::string id = xmlDim->Attribute("id");
428 uint32_t value = strtol(xmlDim->Attribute("value"), NULL__null, 10);
429
430 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Loading dimension %s\n", id.c_str());
431
432 m_dimensions_by_id[id] = value;
433 xmlDim = xmlDim->NextSiblingElement();
434 }
435 }
436
437 // Load colors
438 {
439 TiXmlElement* xmlColor = handle
440 .FirstChild("theme")
441 .FirstChild("colors")
442 .FirstChild("color").ToElement();
443 while (xmlColor) {
444 std::string id = xmlColor->Attribute("id");
445 uint32_t value = strtol(xmlColor->Attribute("value")+1, NULL__null, 16);
446 gfx::Color color = gfx::rgba(
447 (value & 0xff0000) >> 16,
448 (value & 0xff00) >> 8,
449 (value & 0xff));
450
451 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Loading color %s\n", id.c_str());
452
453 m_colors_by_id[id] = color;
454 xmlColor = xmlColor->NextSiblingElement();
455 }
456 }
457
458 // Load parts
459 {
460 TiXmlElement* xmlPart = handle
461 .FirstChild("theme")
462 .FirstChild("parts")
463 .FirstChild("part").ToElement();
464 while (xmlPart) {
465 // Get the tool-icon rectangle
466 const char* part_id = xmlPart->Attribute("id");
467 int x = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("x"), nullptr, 10);
468 int y = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("y"), nullptr, 10);
469 int w = (xmlPart->Attribute("w") ? scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("w"), nullptr, 10): 0);
470 int h = (xmlPart->Attribute("h") ? scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("h"), nullptr, 10): 0);
471
472 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Loading part %s\n", part_id);
473
474 SkinPartPtr part = m_parts_by_id[part_id];
475 if (!part)
476 part = m_parts_by_id[part_id] = SkinPartPtr(new SkinPart);
477
478 if (w > 0 && h > 0) {
479 part->setSpriteBounds(gfx::Rect(x, y, w, h));
480 part->setBitmap(0, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(0), gfx::Rect(x, y, w, h)));
481 }
482 else if (xmlPart->Attribute("w1")) { // 3x3-1 part (NW, N, NE, E, SE, S, SW, W)
483 int w1 = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("w1"), nullptr, 10);
484 int w2 = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("w2"), nullptr, 10);
485 int w3 = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("w3"), nullptr, 10);
486 int h1 = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("h1"), nullptr, 10);
487 int h2 = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("h2"), nullptr, 10);
488 int h3 = scale*strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("h3"), nullptr, 10);
489
490 part->setSpriteBounds(gfx::Rect(x, y, w1+w2+w3, h1+h2+h3));
491 part->setSlicesBounds(gfx::Rect(w1, h1, w2, h2));
492
493 part->setBitmap(0, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(0), gfx::Rect(x, y, w1, h1))); // NW
494 part->setBitmap(1, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(1), gfx::Rect(x+w1, y, w2, h1))); // N
495 part->setBitmap(2, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(2), gfx::Rect(x+w1+w2, y, w3, h1))); // NE
496 part->setBitmap(3, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(3), gfx::Rect(x+w1+w2, y+h1, w3, h2))); // E
497 part->setBitmap(4, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(4), gfx::Rect(x+w1+w2, y+h1+h2, w3, h3))); // SE
498 part->setBitmap(5, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(5), gfx::Rect(x+w1, y+h1+h2, w2, h3))); // S
499 part->setBitmap(6, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(6), gfx::Rect(x, y+h1+h2, w1, h3))); // SW
500 part->setBitmap(7, sliceSheet(part->bitmap(7), gfx::Rect(x, y+h1, w1, h2))); // W
501 }
502
503 // Is it a mouse cursor?
504 if (std::strncmp(part_id, "cursor_", 7) == 0) {
505 std::string cursorName = std::string(part_id).substr(7);
506 int focusx = scale*std::strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("focusx"), NULL__null, 10);
507 int focusy = scale*std::strtol(xmlPart->Attribute("focusy"), NULL__null, 10);
508
509 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Loading cursor '%s'\n", cursorName.c_str());
510
511 auto it = m_cursors.find(cursorName);
512 if (it != m_cursors.end() && it->second != nullptr) {
513 delete it->second;
514 it->second = nullptr;
515 }
516
517 // TODO share the Surface with the SkinPart
518 os::Surface* slice = sliceSheet(nullptr, gfx::Rect(x, y, w, h));
519 Cursor* cursor =
520 new Cursor(slice, gfx::Point(focusx, focusy));
521 m_cursors[cursorName] = cursor;
522
523 for (int c=0; c<kCursorTypes; ++c) {
524 if (cursorName == g_cursor_names[c]) {
525 m_standardCursors[c] = cursor;
526 break;
527 }
528 }
529 }
530
531 xmlPart = xmlPart->NextSiblingElement();
532 }
533 }
534
535 // Load styles
536 {
537 TiXmlElement* xmlStyle = handle
538 .FirstChild("theme")
539 .FirstChild("styles")
540 .FirstChild("style").ToElement();
541
542 if (!xmlStyle) // Without styles?
543 throw base::Exception("There are no styles");
544
545 while (xmlStyle) {
546 const char* style_id = xmlStyle->Attribute("id");
547 if (!style_id) {
548 throw base::Exception("<style> without 'id' attribute in '%s'\n",
549 xml_filename.c_str());
550 }
551
552 const char* extends_id = xmlStyle->Attribute("extends");
553 const ui::Style* base = nullptr;
554 if (extends_id)
555 base = m_styles[extends_id];
556
557 if (backward)
558 backward->notifyStyleExistence(style_id);
559
560 ui::Style* style = m_styles[style_id];
561 if (!style) {
562 m_styles[style_id] = style = new ui::Style(base);
563 }
564 else {
565 *style = ui::Style(base);
566 }
567 style->setId(style_id);
568
569 // Margin
570 {
571 const char* m = xmlStyle->Attribute("margin");
572 const char* l = xmlStyle->Attribute("margin-left");
573 const char* t = xmlStyle->Attribute("margin-top");
574 const char* r = xmlStyle->Attribute("margin-right");
575 const char* b = xmlStyle->Attribute("margin-bottom");
576 gfx::Border margin = ui::Style::UndefinedBorder();
577 if (m || l) margin.left(scale*std::strtol(l ? l: m, nullptr, 10));
578 if (m || t) margin.top(scale*std::strtol(t ? t: m, nullptr, 10));
579 if (m || r) margin.right(scale*std::strtol(r ? r: m, nullptr, 10));
580 if (m || b) margin.bottom(scale*std::strtol(b ? b: m, nullptr, 10));
581 style->setMargin(margin);
582 }
583
584 // Border
585 {
586 const char* m = xmlStyle->Attribute("border");
587 const char* l = xmlStyle->Attribute("border-left");
588 const char* t = xmlStyle->Attribute("border-top");
589 const char* r = xmlStyle->Attribute("border-right");
590 const char* b = xmlStyle->Attribute("border-bottom");
591 gfx::Border border = ui::Style::UndefinedBorder();
592 if (m || l) border.left(scale*std::strtol(l ? l: m, nullptr, 10));
593 if (m || t) border.top(scale*std::strtol(t ? t: m, nullptr, 10));
594 if (m || r) border.right(scale*std::strtol(r ? r: m, nullptr, 10));
595 if (m || b) border.bottom(scale*std::strtol(b ? b: m, nullptr, 10));
596 style->setBorder(border);
597 }
598
599 // Padding
600 {
601 const char* m = xmlStyle->Attribute("padding");
602 const char* l = xmlStyle->Attribute("padding-left");
603 const char* t = xmlStyle->Attribute("padding-top");
604 const char* r = xmlStyle->Attribute("padding-right");
605 const char* b = xmlStyle->Attribute("padding-bottom");
606 gfx::Border padding = ui::Style::UndefinedBorder();
607 if (m || l) padding.left(scale*std::strtol(l ? l: m, nullptr, 10));
608 if (m || t) padding.top(scale*std::strtol(t ? t: m, nullptr, 10));
609 if (m || r) padding.right(scale*std::strtol(r ? r: m, nullptr, 10));
610 if (m || b) padding.bottom(scale*std::strtol(b ? b: m, nullptr, 10));
611 style->setPadding(padding);
612 }
613
614 // Font
615 {
616 const char* fontId = xmlStyle->Attribute("font");
617 if (fontId) {
618 os::Font* font = m_themeFonts[fontId];
619 style->setFont(font);
620 }
621 }
622
623 TiXmlElement* xmlLayer = xmlStyle->FirstChildElement();
624 while (xmlLayer) {
625 const std::string layerName = xmlLayer->Value();
626
627 LOG(VERBOSE, "THEME: Layer %s for %s\n", layerName.c_str(), style_id);
628
629 ui::Style::Layer layer;
630
631 // Layer type
632 if (layerName == "background") {
633 layer.setType(ui::Style::Layer::Type::kBackground);
634 }
635 else if (layerName == "background-border") {
636 layer.setType(ui::Style::Layer::Type::kBackgroundBorder);
637 }
638 else if (layerName == "border") {
639 layer.setType(ui::Style::Layer::Type::kBorder);
640 }
641 else if (layerName == "icon") {
642 layer.setType(ui::Style::Layer::Type::kIcon);
643 }
644 else if (layerName == "text") {
645 layer.setType(ui::Style::Layer::Type::kText);
646 }
647 else if (layerName == "newlayer") {
648 layer.setType(ui::Style::Layer::Type::kNewLayer);
649 }
650
651 // Parse state condition
652 const char* stateValue = xmlLayer->Attribute("state");
653 if (stateValue) {
654 std::string state(stateValue);
655 int flags = 0;
656 if (state.find("disabled") != std::string::npos) flags |= ui::Style::Layer::kDisabled;
657 if (state.find("selected") != std::string::npos) flags |= ui::Style::Layer::kSelected;
658 if (state.find("focus") != std::string::npos) flags |= ui::Style::Layer::kFocus;
659 if (state.find("mouse") != std::string::npos) flags |= ui::Style::Layer::kMouse;
660 layer.setFlags(flags);
661 }
662
663 // Align
664 const char* alignValue = xmlLayer->Attribute("align");
665 if (alignValue) {
666 std::string alignString(alignValue);
667 int align = 0;
668 if (alignString.find("left") != std::string::npos) align |= LEFT;
669 if (alignString.find("center") != std::string::npos) align |= CENTER;
670 if (alignString.find("right") != std::string::npos) align |= RIGHT;
671 if (alignString.find("top") != std::string::npos) align |= TOP;
672 if (alignString.find("middle") != std::string::npos) align |= MIDDLE;
673 if (alignString.find("bottom") != std::string::npos) align |= BOTTOM;
674 if (alignString.find("wordwrap") != std::string::npos) align |= WORDWRAP;
675 layer.setAlign(align);
676 }
677
678 // Color
679 const char* colorId = xmlLayer->Attribute("color");
680 if (colorId) {
681 auto it = m_colors_by_id.find(colorId);
682 if (it != m_colors_by_id.end())
683 layer.setColor(it->second);
684 else if (std::strcmp(colorId, "none") == 0) {
685 layer.setColor(gfx::ColorNone);
686 }
687 else {
688 throw base::Exception("Color <%s color='%s' ...> was not found in '%s'\n",
689 layerName.c_str(), colorId,
690 xml_filename.c_str());
691 }
692 }
693
694 // Offset
695 const char* x = xmlLayer->Attribute("x");
696 const char* y = xmlLayer->Attribute("y");
697 if (x || y) {
698 gfx::Point offset(0, 0);
699 if (x) offset.x = std::strtol(x, nullptr, 10);
700 if (y) offset.y = std::strtol(y, nullptr, 10);
701 layer.setOffset(offset*scale);
702 }
703
704 // Sprite sheet
705 const char* partId = xmlLayer->Attribute("part");
706 if (partId) {
707 auto it = m_parts_by_id.find(partId);
708 if (it != m_parts_by_id.end()) {
709 SkinPartPtr part = it->second;
710 if (part) {
711 if (layer.type() == ui::Style::Layer::Type::kIcon)
712 layer.setIcon(part->bitmap(0));
713 else {
714 layer.setSpriteSheet(m_sheet);
715 layer.setSpriteBounds(part->spriteBounds());
716 layer.setSlicesBounds(part->slicesBounds());
717 }
718 }
719 }
720 else if (std::strcmp(partId, "none") == 0) {
721 layer.setIcon(nullptr);
722 layer.setSpriteSheet(nullptr);
723 layer.setSpriteBounds(gfx::Rect(0, 0, 0, 0));
724 layer.setSlicesBounds(gfx::Rect(0, 0, 0, 0));
725 }
726 else {
727 throw base::Exception("Part <%s part='%s' ...> was not found in '%s'\n",
728 layerName.c_str(), partId,
729 xml_filename.c_str());
730 }
731 }
732
733 if (layer.type() != ui::Style::Layer::Type::kNone)
734 style->addLayer(layer);
735
736 xmlLayer = xmlLayer->NextSiblingElement();
737 }
738
739 xmlStyle = xmlStyle->NextSiblingElement();
740 }
741 }
742
743 if (backward)
744 backward->createMissingStyles(this);
745
746 ThemeFile<SkinTheme>::updateInternals();
747}
748
749os::Surface* SkinTheme::sliceSheet(os::Surface* sur, const gfx::Rect& bounds)
750{
751 if (sur && (sur->width() != bounds.w ||
752 sur->height() != bounds.h)) {
753 sur->dispose();
754 sur = nullptr;
755 }
756
757 if (!bounds.isEmpty()) {
758 if (!sur)
759 sur = os::instance()->createRgbaSurface(bounds.w, bounds.h);
760
761 os::SurfaceLock lockSrc(m_sheet);
762 os::SurfaceLock lockDst(sur);
763 m_sheet->blitTo(sur, bounds.x, bounds.y, 0, 0, bounds.w, bounds.h);
764 }
765 else {
766 ASSERT(!sur);
767 }
768
769 return sur;
770}
771
772os::Font* SkinTheme::getWidgetFont(const Widget* widget) const
773{
774 auto skinPropery = std::static_pointer_cast<SkinProperty>(widget->getProperty(SkinProperty::Name));
775 if (skinPropery && skinPropery->hasMiniFont())
776 return getMiniFont();
777 else
778 return getDefaultFont();
779}
780
781Cursor* SkinTheme::getStandardCursor(CursorType type)
782{
783 if (type >= kFirstCursorType && type <= kLastCursorType)
784 return m_standardCursors[type];
785 else
786 return nullptr;
787}

789void SkinTheme::initWidget(Widget* widget)
790{
791#define BORDER(n)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(n)) \
792 widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(n))
793
794#define BORDER4(L,T,R,B)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((L), (T), (R), (B))) \
795 widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((L), (T), (R), (B)))
796
797 const int scale = guiscale();
798
799 switch (widget->type()) {
800
801 case kBoxWidget:
802 widget->setStyle(styles.box());
803 BORDER(0)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(0));
804 widget->setChildSpacing(4 * scale);
805 break;
806
807 case kButtonWidget:
808 widget->setStyle(styles.button());
809 break;
810
811 case kCheckWidget:
812 widget->setStyle(styles.checkBox());
813 break;
814
815 case kRadioWidget:
816 widget->setStyle(styles.radioButton());
817 break;
818
819 case kEntryWidget:
820 BORDER4(widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapW
()->width()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapN()->height
()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapE()->width()), (parts
.sunkenNormal()->bitmapS()->height())))
821 parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapW()->width(),widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapW
()->width()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapN()->height
()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapE()->width()), (parts
.sunkenNormal()->bitmapS()->height())))
822 parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapN()->height(),widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapW
()->width()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapN()->height
()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapE()->width()), (parts
.sunkenNormal()->bitmapS()->height())))
823 parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapE()->width(),widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapW
()->width()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapN()->height
()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapE()->width()), (parts
.sunkenNormal()->bitmapS()->height())))
824 parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapS()->height())widget->setBorder(gfx::Border((parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapW
()->width()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapN()->height
()), (parts.sunkenNormal()->bitmapE()->width()), (parts
.sunkenNormal()->bitmapS()->height())));
825 widget->setChildSpacing(3 * scale);
826 break;
827
828 case kGridWidget:
829 widget->setStyle(styles.grid());
830 BORDER(0)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(0));
831 widget->setChildSpacing(4 * scale);
832 break;
833
834 case kLabelWidget:
835 widget->setStyle(styles.label());
836 break;
837
838 case kLinkLabelWidget:
839 widget->setStyle(styles.link());
840 break;
841
842 case kListBoxWidget:
843 BORDER(0)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(0));
844 widget->setChildSpacing(0);
845 break;
846
847 case kListItemWidget:
848 widget->setStyle(styles.listItem());
849 break;
850
851 case kComboBoxWidget: {
852 ComboBox* combobox = static_cast<ComboBox*>(widget);
853 Button* button = combobox->getButtonWidget();
854 combobox->setChildSpacing(0);
855 button->setStyle(styles.comboboxButton());
856 break;
857 }
858
859 case kMenuWidget:
860 widget->setStyle(styles.menu());
861 break;
862
863 case kMenuBarWidget:
864 widget->setStyle(styles.menubar());
865 break;
866
867 case kMenuBoxWidget:
868 widget->setStyle(styles.menubox());
869 break;
870
871 case kMenuItemWidget:
872 BORDER(2 * scale)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(2 * scale));
873 widget->setChildSpacing(18 * scale);
874 break;
875
876 case kSplitterWidget:
877 widget->setChildSpacing(3 * scale);
878 widget->setStyle(styles.splitter());
879 break;
880
881 case kSeparatorWidget:
882 // Horizontal bar
883 if (widget->align() & HORIZONTAL) {
884 if (dynamic_cast<MenuSeparator*>(widget)) {
885 widget->setStyle(styles.menuSeparator());
886 BORDER(2 * scale)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(2 * scale));
887 }
888 else
889 widget->setStyle(styles.horizontalSeparator());
890 }
891 // Vertical bar
892 else {
893 widget->setStyle(styles.verticalSeparator());
894 }
895 break;
896
897 case kSliderWidget:
898 widget->setStyle(styles.slider());
899 break;
900
901 case kTextBoxWidget:
902 BORDER(4*guiscale())widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(4*guiscale()));
903 widget->setChildSpacing(0);
904 widget->setBgColor(colors.textboxFace());
905 break;
906
907 case kViewWidget:
908 widget->setChildSpacing(0);
909 widget->setBgColor(colors.windowFace());
910 widget->setStyle(styles.view());
911 break;
912
913 case kViewScrollbarWidget:
914 widget->setStyle(styles.scrollbar());
915 static_cast<ScrollBar*>(widget)->setThumbStyle(styles.scrollbarThumb());
916 break;
917
918 case kViewViewportWidget:
919 BORDER(0)widget->setBorder(gfx::Border(0));
920 widget->setChildSpacing(0);
921 break;
922
923 case kManagerWidget:
924 widget->setStyle(styles.desktop());
925 break;
926
927 case kWindowWidget:
928 if (TipWindow* window = dynamic_cast<TipWindow*>(widget)) {
929 window->setStyle(styles.tooltipWindow());
930 window->setArrowStyle(styles.tooltipWindowArrow());
931 window->textBox()->setStyle(SkinTheme::instance()->styles.tooltipText());
932 }
933 else if (dynamic_cast<TransparentPopupWindow*>(widget)) {
934 widget->setStyle(styles.transparentPopupWindow());
935 }
936 else if (dynamic_cast<PopupWindow*>(widget)) {
937 widget->setStyle(styles.popupWindow());
938 }
939 else if (static_cast<Window*>(widget)->isDesktop()) {
940 widget->setStyle(styles.desktop());
941 }
942 else {
943 if (widget->hasText()) {
944 widget->setStyle(styles.windowWithTitle());
945 }
946 else {
947 widget->setStyle(styles.windowWithoutTitle());
948 }
949 }
950 break;
951
952 case kWindowTitleLabelWidget:
953 widget->setStyle(SkinTheme::instance()->styles.windowTitleLabel());
954 break;
955
956 case kWindowCloseButtonWidget:
957 widget->setStyle(SkinTheme::instance()->styles.windowCloseButton());
958 break;
959
960 default:
961 break;
962 }
963}

983void SkinTheme::paintEntry(PaintEvent& ev)
984{
985 Graphics* g = ev.graphics();
986 Entry* widget = static_cast<Entry*>(ev.getSource());
987 gfx::Rect bounds = widget->clientBounds();
988
989 // Outside borders
990 g->fillRect(BGCOLOR(getWidgetBgColor(widget)), bounds);
991
992 bool isMiniLook = false;
993 auto skinPropery = std::static_pointer_cast<SkinProperty>(widget->getProperty(SkinProperty::Name));
994 if (skinPropery)
995 isMiniLook = (skinPropery->getLook() == MiniLook);
996
997 drawRect(g, bounds,
998 (widget->hasFocus() ?
999 (isMiniLook ? parts.sunkenMiniFocused().get(): parts.sunkenFocused().get()):
1000 (isMiniLook ? parts.sunkenMiniNormal().get() : parts.sunkenNormal().get())));
1001
1002 drawEntryText(g, widget);
1003}
1004
1005namespace {
1006
1007class DrawEntryTextDelegate : public os::DrawTextDelegate {
1008public:
1009 DrawEntryTextDelegate(Entry* widget, Graphics* graphics,
1010 const gfx::Point& pos, const int h)
1011 : m_widget(widget)
1012 , m_graphics(graphics)
1013 , m_caretDrawn(false)
1014 // m_lastX is an absolute position on screen
1015 , m_lastX(pos.x+m_widget->bounds().x)
1016 , m_y(pos.y)
1017 , m_h(h)
1018 {
1019 m_widget->getEntryThemeInfo(&m_index, &m_caret, &m_state, &m_range);
1020 }
1021
1022 int index() const { return m_index; }
1023 bool caretDrawn() const { return m_caretDrawn; }
1024 const gfx::Rect& textBounds() const { return m_textBounds; }
1025
1026 void preProcessChar(const int index,
1027 const int codepoint,
1028 gfx::Color& fg,
1029 gfx::Color& bg,
1030 const gfx::Rect& charBounds) override {
1031 // Normal text
1032 auto& colors = SkinTheme::instance()->colors;
1033 bg = ColorNone;
1034 fg = colors.text();
1035
1036 // Selected
1037 if ((m_index >= m_range.from) &&
1038 (m_index < m_range.to)) {
1039 if (m_widget->hasFocus())
1040 bg = colors.selected();
1041 else
1042 bg = colors.disabled();
1043 fg = colors.selectedText();
1044 }
1045
1046 // Disabled
1047 if (!m_widget->isEnabled()) {
1048 bg = ColorNone;
1049 fg = colors.disabled();
1050 }
1051
1052 m_bg = bg;
1053 }
1054
1055 bool preDrawChar(const gfx::Rect& charBounds) override {
1056 m_textBounds |= charBounds;
1057 m_charStartX = charBounds.x;
1058
1059 if (charBounds.x2()-m_widget->bounds().x < m_widget->clientBounds().x2()) {
1060 if (m_bg != ColorNone) {
1061 // Fill background e.g. needed for selected/highlighted
1062 // regions with TTF fonts where the char is smaller than the
1063 // text bounds [m_y,m_y+m_h)
1064 gfx::Rect fillThisRect(m_lastX-m_widget->bounds().x,
1065 m_y, charBounds.x2()-m_lastX, m_h);
1066 if (charBounds != fillThisRect)
1067 m_graphics->fillRect(m_bg, fillThisRect);
1068 }
1069 m_lastX = charBounds.x2();
1070 return true;
1071 }
1072 else
1073 return false;
1074 }
1075
1076 void postDrawChar(const gfx::Rect& charBounds) override {
1077 // Caret
1078 if (m_state &&
1079 m_index == m_caret &&
1080 m_widget->hasFocus() &&
1081 m_widget->isEnabled()) {
1082 SkinTheme::instance()->drawEntryCaret(
1083 m_graphics, m_widget,
1084 m_charStartX-m_widget->bounds().x, m_y);
1085 m_caretDrawn = true;
1086 }
1087
1088 ++m_index;
1089 }
1090
1091private:
1092 Entry* m_widget;
1093 Graphics* m_graphics;
1094 int m_index;
1095 int m_caret;
1096 int m_state;
1097 Entry::Range m_range;
1098 gfx::Rect m_textBounds;
1099 bool m_caretDrawn;
1100 gfx::Color m_bg;
1101 int m_lastX; // Last position used to fill the background
1102 int m_y, m_h;
1103 int m_charStartX;
1104};
1105
1106} // anonymous namespace
1107
1108void SkinTheme::drawEntryText(ui::Graphics* g, ui::Entry* widget)
1109{
1110 // Draw the text
1111 gfx::Rect bounds = widget->getEntryTextBounds();
1112
1113 DrawEntryTextDelegate delegate(widget, g, bounds.origin(), widget->textHeight());
1114 int scroll = delegate.index();
1115
1116 const std::string& textString = widget->text();
1117 base::utf8_const_iterator utf8_it((textString.begin()));
1118 int textlen = base::utf8_length(textString);
1119 scroll = std::min(scroll, textlen);
1120 if (scroll)
1121 utf8_it += scroll;
1122
1123 g->drawText(utf8_it,
1124 base::utf8_const_iterator(textString.end()),
1125 colors.text(), ColorNone,
1126 bounds.origin(), &delegate);
1127
1128 bounds.x += delegate.textBounds().w;
1129
1130 // Draw suffix if there is enough space
1131 if (!widget->getSuffix().empty()) {
1132 Rect sufBounds(bounds.x, bounds.y,
1133 bounds.x2()-widget->childSpacing()*guiscale()-bounds.x,
1134 widget->textHeight());
1135 IntersectClip clip(g, sufBounds & widget->clientChildrenBounds());
1136 if (clip) {
1137 drawText(
1138 g, widget->getSuffix().c_str(),
1139 colors.entrySuffix(), ColorNone,
1140 widget, sufBounds, widget->align(), 0);
1141 }
1142 }
1143
1144 // Draw caret at the end of the text
1145 if (!delegate.caretDrawn()) {
1146 gfx::Rect charBounds(bounds.x+widget->bounds().x,
1147 bounds.y+widget->bounds().y, 0, widget->textHeight());
1148 delegate.preDrawChar(charBounds);
1149 delegate.postDrawChar(charBounds);
1150 }
1151}

1153void SkinTheme::paintListBox(PaintEvent& ev)

1155 Graphics* g = ev.graphics();
1156
1157 g->fillRect(colors.background(), g->getClipBounds());
1158}

1167
1168void SkinTheme::paintMenuItem(ui::PaintEvent& ev)
1169{
1170 int scale = guiscale();
1171 Graphics* g = ev.graphics();
1172 MenuItem* widget = static_cast<MenuItem*>(ev.getSource());
1173 gfx::Rect bounds = widget->clientBounds();
1174 gfx::Color fg, bg;
1175 int c, bar;
1176
1177 // TODO ASSERT?
1178 if (!widget->parent()->parent())
1179 return;
1180
1181 bar = (widget->parent()->parent()->type() == kMenuBarWidget);
1182
1183 // Colors
1184 if (!widget->isEnabled()) {
1185 fg = ColorNone;
1186 bg = colors.menuitemNormalFace();
1187 }
1188 else {
1189 if (widget->isHighlighted()) {
1190 fg = colors.menuitemHighlightText();
1191 bg = colors.menuitemHighlightFace();
1192 }
1193 else if (widget->hasMouse()) {
1194 fg = colors.menuitemHotText();
1195 bg = colors.menuitemHotFace();
1196 }
1197 else {
1198 fg = colors.menuitemNormalText();
1199 bg = colors.menuitemNormalFace();
1200 }
1201 }
1202
1203 // Background
1204 g->fillRect(bg, bounds);
1205
1206 // Draw an indicator for selected items
1207 if (widget->isSelected()) {
1208 os::Surface* icon =
1209 (widget->isEnabled() ?
1210 parts.checkSelected()->bitmap(0):
1211 parts.checkDisabled()->bitmap(0));
1212
1213 int x = bounds.x+4*scale-icon->width()/2;
1214 int y = bounds.y+bounds.h/2-icon->height()/2;
1215 g->drawRgbaSurface(icon, x, y);
1216 }
1217
1218 // Text
1219 if (bar)
1220 widget->setAlign(CENTER | MIDDLE);
1221 else
1222 widget->setAlign(LEFT | MIDDLE);
1223
1224 Rect pos = bounds;
1225 if (!bar)
1226 pos.offset(widget->childSpacing()/2, 0);
1227 drawText(g, nullptr, fg, ColorNone, widget, pos,
1228 widget->align(), widget->mnemonic());
1229
1230 // For menu-box
1231 if (!bar) {
1232 // Draw the arrown (to indicate which this menu has a sub-menu)
1233 if (widget->getSubmenu()) {
1234 // Enabled
1235 if (widget->isEnabled()) {
1236 for (c=0; c<3*scale; c++)
1237 g->drawVLine(fg,
1238 bounds.x2()-3*scale-c,
1239 bounds.y+bounds.h/2-c, 2*c+1);
1240 }
1241 // Disabled
1242 else {
1243 for (c=0; c<3*scale; c++)
1244 g->drawVLine(colors.background(),
1245 bounds.x2()-3*scale-c+1,
1246 bounds.y+bounds.h/2-c+1, 2*c+1);
1247
1248 for (c=0; c<3*scale; c++)
1249 g->drawVLine(colors.disabled(),
1250 bounds.x2()-3*scale-c,
1251 bounds.y+bounds.h/2-c, 2*c+1);
1252 }
1253 }
1254 // Draw the keyboard shortcut
1255 else if (AppMenuItem* appMenuItem = dynamic_cast<AppMenuItem*>(widget)) {
1256 if (appMenuItem->key() && !appMenuItem->key()->accels().empty()) {
1257 int old_align = appMenuItem->align();
1258
1259 pos = bounds;
1260 pos.w -= widget->childSpacing()/4;
1261
1262 std::string buf = appMenuItem->key()->accels().front().toString();
1263
1264 widget->setAlign(RIGHT | MIDDLE);
1265 drawText(g, buf.c_str(), fg, ColorNone, widget, pos, widget->align(), 0);
1266 widget->setAlign(old_align);
1267 }
1268 }
1269 }
1270}
1271
1272void SkinTheme::paintSlider(PaintEvent& ev)
1273{
1274 Graphics* g = ev.graphics();
1275 Slider* widget = static_cast<Slider*>(ev.getSource());
1276 const Rect bounds = widget->clientBounds();
1277 int min, max, value;
1278
1279 // Outside borders
1280 gfx::Color bgcolor = widget->bgColor();
1281 if (!is_transparent(bgcolor))
1282 g->fillRect(bgcolor, bounds);
1283
1284 widget->getSliderThemeInfo(&min, &max, &value);
1285
1286 Rect rc = bounds;
1287 rc.shrink(widget->border());
1288 int x;
1289 if (min != max)
1290 x = rc.x + rc.w * (value-min) / (max-min);
1291 else
1292 x = rc.x;
1293
1294 rc = bounds;
1295
1296 // The mini-look is used for sliders with tiny borders.
1297 bool isMiniLook = false;
1298
1299 // The BG painter is used for sliders without a number-indicator and
1300 // customized background (e.g. RGB sliders)
1301 ISliderBgPainter* bgPainter = NULL__null;
1302
1303 const auto skinPropery = std::static_pointer_cast<SkinProperty>(widget->getProperty(SkinProperty::Name));
1304 if (skinPropery)
1305 isMiniLook = (skinPropery->getLook() == MiniLook);
1306
1307 const auto skinSliderPropery = std::static_pointer_cast<SkinSliderProperty>(widget->getProperty(SkinSliderProperty::Name));
1308 if (skinSliderPropery)
1309 bgPainter = skinSliderPropery->getBgPainter();
1310
1311 // Draw customized background
1312 if (bgPainter) {
1313 SkinPartPtr nw = parts.miniSliderEmpty();
1314 os::Surface* thumb =
1315 (widget->hasFocus() ? parts.miniSliderThumbFocused()->bitmap(0):
1316 parts.miniSliderThumb()->bitmap(0));
1317
1318 // Draw background
1319 g->fillRect(BGCOLOR(getWidgetBgColor(widget)), rc);
1320
1321 // Draw thumb
1322 int thumb_y = rc.y;
1323 if (rc.h > thumb->height()*3)
1324 rc.shrink(Border(0, thumb->height(), 0, 0));
1325
1326 // Draw borders
1327 if (rc.h > 4*guiscale()) {
1328 rc.shrink(Border(3, 0, 3, 1) * guiscale());
1329 drawRect(g, rc, nw.get());
1330 }
1331
1332 // Draw background (using the customized ISliderBgPainter implementation)
1333 rc.shrink(Border(1, 1, 1, 2) * guiscale());
1334 if (!rc.isEmpty())
1335 bgPainter->paint(widget, g, rc);
1336
1337 g->drawRgbaSurface(thumb, x-thumb->width()/2, thumb_y);
1338 }
1339 else {
1340 // Draw borders
1341 SkinPartPtr full_part;
1342 SkinPartPtr empty_part;
1343
1344 if (isMiniLook) {
1345 full_part = widget->hasMouseOver() ? parts.miniSliderFullFocused():
1346 parts.miniSliderFull();
1347 empty_part = widget->hasMouseOver() ? parts.miniSliderEmptyFocused():
1348 parts.miniSliderEmpty();
1349 }
1350 else {
1351 full_part = widget->hasFocus() ? parts.sliderFullFocused():
1352 parts.sliderFull();
1353 empty_part = widget->hasFocus() ? parts.sliderEmptyFocused():
1354 parts.sliderEmpty();
1355 }
1356
1357 if (value == min)
1358 drawRect(g, rc, empty_part.get());
1359 else if (value == max)
1360 drawRect(g, rc, full_part.get());
1361 else
1362 drawRect2(g, rc, x,
1363 full_part.get(), empty_part.get());
1364
1365 // Draw text
1366 std::string old_text = widget->text();
1367 widget->setTextQuiet(widget->convertValueToText(value));
1368
1369 gfx::Rect textrc;
1370 int textAlign;
1371 calcTextInfo(widget, widget->style(), bounds, textrc, textAlign);
1372
1373 {
1374 IntersectClip clip(g, Rect(rc.x, rc.y, x-rc.x+1, rc.h));
1375 if (clip) {
1376 drawText(g, nullptr,
1377 colors.sliderFullText(), ColorNone,
1378 widget, textrc, textAlign, widget->mnemonic());
1379 }
1380 }
1381
1382 {
1383 IntersectClip clip(g, Rect(x+1, rc.y, rc.w-(x-rc.x+1), rc.h));
1384 if (clip) {
1385 drawText(g, nullptr,
1386 colors.sliderEmptyText(),
1387 ColorNone, widget, textrc, textAlign, widget->mnemonic());
1388 }
1389 }
1390
1391 widget->setTextQuiet(old_text.c_str());
1392 }
1393}

1430
1431gfx::Color SkinTheme::getWidgetBgColor(Widget* widget)
1432{
1433 gfx::Color c = widget->bgColor();
1434 bool decorative = widget->isDecorative();
1435
1436 if (!is_transparent(c) ||
1437 widget->type() == kWindowWidget)
1438 return (widget->isTransparent() ? gfx::ColorNone: c);
1439 else if (decorative)
1440 return colors.selected();
1441 else
1442 return colors.face();
1443}
1444
1445void SkinTheme::drawText(Graphics* g, const char* t,
1446 const gfx::Color fgColor,
1447 const gfx::Color bgColor,
1448 const Widget* widget,
1449 const Rect& rc,
1450 const int textAlign,
1451 const int mnemonic)
1452{
1453 if (t || widget->hasText()) {
1454 Rect textrc;
1455
1456 g->setFont(widget->font());
1457
1458 if (!t)
1459 t = widget->text().c_str();
1460
1461 textrc.setSize(g->measureUIText(t));
1462
1463 // Horizontally text alignment
1464
1465 if (textAlign & RIGHT)
1466 textrc.x = rc.x + rc.w - textrc.w - 1;
1467 else if (textAlign & CENTER)
1468 textrc.x = rc.center().x - textrc.w/2;
1469 else
1470 textrc.x = rc.x;
1471
1472 // Vertically text alignment
1473
1474 if (textAlign & BOTTOM)
1475 textrc.y = rc.y + rc.h - textrc.h - 1;
1476 else if (textAlign & MIDDLE)
1477 textrc.y = rc.center().y - textrc.h/2;
1478 else
1479 textrc.y = rc.y;
1480
1481 // Background
1482 if (!is_transparent(bgColor)) {
1483 if (!widget->isEnabled())
1484 g->fillRect(bgColor, Rect(textrc).inflate(guiscale(), guiscale()));
1485 else
1486 g->fillRect(bgColor, textrc);
1487 }
1488
1489 // Text
1490 Rect textWrap = textrc.createIntersection(
1491 // TODO add ui::Widget::getPadding() property
1492 // Rect(widget->clientBounds()).shrink(widget->border()));
1493 widget->clientBounds()).inflate(0, 1*guiscale());
1494
1495 IntersectClip clip(g, textWrap);
1496 if (clip) {
1497 if (!widget->isEnabled()) {
1498 // Draw white part
1499 g->drawUIText(
1500 t,
1501 colors.background(),
1502 gfx::ColorNone,
1503 textrc.origin() + Point(guiscale(), guiscale()),
1504 mnemonic);
1505 }
1506
1507 g->drawUIText(
1508 t,
1509 (!widget->isEnabled() ?
1510 colors.disabled():
1511 (gfx::geta(fgColor) > 0 ? fgColor :
1512 colors.text())),
1513 bgColor, textrc.origin(),
1514 mnemonic);
1515 }
1516 }
1517}
1518
1519void SkinTheme::drawEntryCaret(ui::Graphics* g, Entry* widget, int x, int y)
1520{
1521 gfx::Color color = colors.text();
1522 int textHeight = widget->textHeight();
1523 gfx::Size caretSize = getEntryCaretSize(widget);
1524
1525 for (int u=x; u<x+caretSize.w; ++u)
1526 g->drawVLine(color, u, y+textHeight/2-caretSize.h/2, caretSize.h);
1527}

1542
1543void SkinTheme::drawRect(Graphics* g, const Rect& rc,
1544 os::Surface* nw, os::Surface* n, os::Surface* ne,
1545 os::Surface* e, os::Surface* se, os::Surface* s,
1546 os::Surface* sw, os::Surface* w)
1547{
1548 int x, y;
1549
1550 // Top
1551
1552 g->drawRgbaSurface(nw, rc.x, rc.y);
1553 {
1554 IntersectClip clip(g, Rect(rc.x+nw->width(), rc.y,
1555 rc.w-nw->width()-ne->width(), rc.h));
1556 if (clip) {
1557 for (x = rc.x+nw->width();
1558 x < rc.x+rc.w-ne->width();
1559 x += n->width()) {
1560 g->drawRgbaSurface(n, x, rc.y);
1561 }
1562 }
1563 }
1564
1565 g->drawRgbaSurface(ne, rc.x+rc.w-ne->width(), rc.y);
1566
1567 // Bottom
1568
1569 g->drawRgbaSurface(sw, rc.x, rc.y+rc.h-sw->height());
1570 {
1571 IntersectClip clip(g, Rect(rc.x+sw->width(), rc.y,
1572 rc.w-sw->width()-se->width(), rc.h));
1573 if (clip) {
1574 for (x = rc.x+sw->width();
1575 x < rc.x+rc.w-se->width();
1576 x += s->width()) {
1577 g->drawRgbaSurface(s, x, rc.y+rc.h-s->height());
1578 }
1579 }
1580 }
1581
1582 g->drawRgbaSurface(se, rc.x+rc.w-se->width(), rc.y+rc.h-se->height());
1583 {
1584 IntersectClip clip(g, Rect(rc.x, rc.y+nw->height(),
1585 rc.w, rc.h-nw->height()-sw->height()));
1586 if (clip) {
1587 // Left
1588 for (y = rc.y+nw->height();
1589 y < rc.y+rc.h-sw->height();
1590 y += w->height()) {
1591 g->drawRgbaSurface(w, rc.x, y);
1592 }
1593
1594 // Right
1595 for (y = rc.y+ne->height();
1596 y < rc.y+rc.h-se->height();
1597 y += e->height()) {
1598 g->drawRgbaSurface(e, rc.x+rc.w-e->width(), y);
1599 }
1600 }
1601 }
1602}

1604void SkinTheme::drawRect(ui::Graphics* g, const gfx::Rect& rc,
1605 SkinPart* skinPart, const bool drawCenter)
1606{
1607 Theme::drawSlices(g, m_sheet, rc,
1608 skinPart->spriteBounds(),
1609 skinPart->slicesBounds(),
1610 gfx::ColorNone,
1611 drawCenter);
1612}
1613
1614void SkinTheme::drawRect2(Graphics* g, const Rect& rc, int x_mid,
1615 SkinPart* nw1, SkinPart* nw2)
1616{
1617 Rect rc2(rc.x, rc.y, x_mid-rc.x+1, rc.h);
1618 {
1619 IntersectClip clip(g, rc2);
1620 if (clip)
1621 drawRect(g, rc, nw1);
1622 }
1623
1624 rc2.x += rc2.w;
1625 rc2.w = rc.w - rc2.w;
1626
1627 IntersectClip clip(g, rc2);
1628 if (clip)
1629 drawRect(g, rc, nw2);
1630}
1631
1632void SkinTheme::drawHline(ui::Graphics* g, const gfx::Rect& rc, SkinPart* part)
1633{
1634 int x;
1635
1636 for (x = rc.x;
1637 x < rc.x2()-part->size().w;
1638 x += part->size().w) {
1639 g->drawRgbaSurface(part->bitmap(0), x, rc.y);
1640 }
1641
1642 if (x < rc.x2()) {
1643 Rect rc2(x, rc.y, rc.w-(x-rc.x), part->size().h);
1644 IntersectClip clip(g, rc2);
1645 if (clip)
1646 g->drawRgbaSurface(part->bitmap(0), x, rc.y);
1647 }
1648}
1649
1650void SkinTheme::drawVline(ui::Graphics* g, const gfx::Rect& rc, SkinPart* part)
1651{
1652 int y;
1653
1654 for (y = rc.y;
1655 y < rc.y2()-part->size().h;
1656 y += part->size().h) {
1657 g->drawRgbaSurface(part->bitmap(0), rc.x, y);
1658 }
1659
1660 if (y < rc.y2()) {
1661 Rect rc2(rc.x, y, part->size().w, rc.h-(y-rc.y));
1662 IntersectClip clip(g, rc2);
1663 if (clip)
1664 g->drawRgbaSurface(part->bitmap(0), rc.x, y);
1665 }
1666}
1667
1668void SkinTheme::paintProgressBar(ui::Graphics* g, const gfx::Rect& rc0, double progress)
1669{
1670 gfx::Color border = colors.text();
1671 border = gfx::rgba(gfx::getr(border),
1672 gfx::getg(border),
1673 gfx::getb(border), 64);
1674 g->drawRect(border, rc0);
1675
1676 gfx::Rect rc = rc0;
1677 rc.shrink(1);
1678
1679 int u = (int)((double)rc.w*progress);
1680 u = base::clamp(u, 0, rc.w);
1681
1682 if (u > 0)
1683 g->fillRect(colors.selected(), gfx::Rect(rc.x, rc.y, u, rc.h));
1684
1685 if (1+u < rc.w)
1686 g->fillRect(colors.background(), gfx::Rect(rc.x+u, rc.y, rc.w-u, rc.h));
1687}
1688
1689std::string SkinTheme::findThemePath(const std::string& themeId) const
1690{
1691 // First we try to find the theme on an extensions
1692 std::string path = App::instance()->extensions().themePath(themeId);
1693 if (path.empty()) {
1694 // Then we try a theme in the old themes/ folder
1695 path = base::join_path(SkinTheme::kThemesFolderName, themeId);
1696 path = base::join_path(path, "theme.xml");
1697
1698 ResourceFinder rf;
1699 rf.includeDataDir(path.c_str());
1700 if (!rf.findFirst())
1701 return std::string();
1702
1703 path = base::get_file_path(rf.filename());
1704 }
1705 return base::normalize_path(path);
1706}

25/** @file bits/basic_string.h
26 * This is an internal header file, included by other library headers.
27 * Do not attempt to use it directly. @headername{string}
28 */
29
30//
31// ISO C++ 14882: 21 Strings library
32//
33
34#ifndef _BASIC_STRING_H1
35#define _BASIC_STRING_H1 1
36
37#pragma GCC system_header
38
39#include <ext/atomicity.h>
40#include <ext/alloc_traits.h>
41#include <debug/debug.h>
42
43#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
44#include <initializer_list>
45#endif
46
47#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201703L
48# include <string_view>
49#endif
50
51
52namespace std _GLIBCXX_VISIBILITY(default)__attribute__ ((__visibility__ ("default")))
53{
54_GLIBCXX_BEGIN_NAMESPACE_VERSION
55
56#if _GLIBCXX_USE_CXX11_ABI1
57_GLIBCXX_BEGIN_NAMESPACE_CXX11namespace __cxx11 {
58 /**
59 * @class basic_string basic_string.h <string>
60 * @brief Managing sequences of characters and character-like objects.
61 *
62 * @ingroup strings
63 * @ingroup sequences
64 *
65 * @tparam _CharT Type of character
66 * @tparam _Traits Traits for character type, defaults to
67 * char_traits<_CharT>.
68 * @tparam _Alloc Allocator type, defaults to allocator<_CharT>.
69 *
70 * Meets the requirements of a <a href="tables.html#65">container</a>, a
71 * <a href="tables.html#66">reversible container</a>, and a
72 * <a href="tables.html#67">sequence</a>. Of the
73 * <a href="tables.html#68">optional sequence requirements</a>, only
74 * @c push_back, @c at, and @c %array access are supported.
75 */
76 template<typename _CharT, typename _Traits, typename _Alloc>
77 class basic_string
78 {
79 typedef typename __gnu_cxx::__alloc_traits<_Alloc>::template
80 rebind<_CharT>::other _Char_alloc_type;
81 typedef __gnu_cxx::__alloc_traits<_Char_alloc_type> _Alloc_traits;
82
83 // Types:
84 public:
85 typedef _Traits traits_type;
86 typedef typename _Traits::char_type value_type;
87 typedef _Char_alloc_type allocator_type;
88 typedef typename _Alloc_traits::size_type size_type;
89 typedef typename _Alloc_traits::difference_type difference_type;
90 typedef typename _Alloc_traits::reference reference;
91 typedef typename _Alloc_traits::const_reference const_reference;
92 typedef typename _Alloc_traits::pointer pointer;
93 typedef typename _Alloc_traits::const_pointer const_pointer;
94 typedef __gnu_cxx::__normal_iterator<pointer, basic_string> iterator;
95 typedef __gnu_cxx::__normal_iterator<const_pointer, basic_string>
96 const_iterator;
97 typedef std::reverse_iterator<const_iterator> const_reverse_iterator;
98 typedef std::reverse_iterator<iterator> reverse_iterator;
99
100 /// Value returned by various member functions when they fail.
101 static const size_type npos = static_cast<size_type>(-1);
102
103 protected:
104 // type used for positions in insert, erase etc.
105#if __cplusplus201103L < 201103L
106 typedef iterator __const_iterator;
107#else
108 typedef const_iterator __const_iterator;
109#endif
110
111 private:
112#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201703L
113 // A helper type for avoiding boiler-plate.
114 typedef basic_string_view<_CharT, _Traits> __sv_type;
115
116 template<typename _Tp, typename _Res>
117 using _If_sv = enable_if_t<
118 __and_<is_convertible<const _Tp&, __sv_type>,
119 __not_<is_convertible<const _Tp*, const basic_string*>>,
120 __not_<is_convertible<const _Tp&, const _CharT*>>>::value,
121 _Res>;
122
123 // Allows an implicit conversion to __sv_type.
124 static __sv_type
125 _S_to_string_view(__sv_type __svt) noexcept
126 { return __svt; }
127
128 // Wraps a string_view by explicit conversion and thus
129 // allows to add an internal constructor that does not
130 // participate in overload resolution when a string_view
131 // is provided.
132 struct __sv_wrapper
133 {
134 explicit __sv_wrapper(__sv_type __sv) noexcept : _M_sv(__sv) { }
135 __sv_type _M_sv;
136 };
137
138 /**
139 * @brief Only internally used: Construct string from a string view
140 * wrapper.
141 * @param __svw string view wrapper.
142 * @param __a Allocator to use.
143 */
144 explicit
145 basic_string(__sv_wrapper __svw, const _Alloc& __a)
146 : basic_string(__svw._M_sv.data(), __svw._M_sv.size(), __a) { }
147#endif
148
149 // Use empty-base optimization: http://www.cantrip.org/emptyopt.html
150 struct _Alloc_hider : allocator_type // TODO check __is_final
151 {
152#if __cplusplus201103L < 201103L
153 _Alloc_hider(pointer __dat, const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
154 : allocator_type(__a), _M_p(__dat) { }
155#else
156 _Alloc_hider(pointer __dat, const _Alloc& __a)
157 : allocator_type(__a), _M_p(__dat) { }
158
159 _Alloc_hider(pointer __dat, _Alloc&& __a = _Alloc())
160 : allocator_type(std::move(__a)), _M_p(__dat) { }
161#endif
162
163 pointer _M_p; // The actual data.
164 };
165
166 _Alloc_hider _M_dataplus;
167 size_type _M_string_length;
168
169 enum { _S_local_capacity = 15 / sizeof(_CharT) };
170
171 union
172 {
173 _CharT _M_local_buf[_S_local_capacity + 1];
174 size_type _M_allocated_capacity;
175 };
176
177 void
178 _M_data(pointer __p)
179 { _M_dataplus._M_p = __p; }
180
181 void
182 _M_length(size_type __length)
183 { _M_string_length = __length; }
184
185 pointer
186 _M_data() const
187 { return _M_dataplus._M_p; }
188
189 pointer
190 _M_local_data()
191 {
192#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
193 return std::pointer_traits<pointer>::pointer_to(*_M_local_buf);
194#else
195 return pointer(_M_local_buf);
196#endif
197 }
198
199 const_pointer
200 _M_local_data() const
201 {
202#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
203 return std::pointer_traits<const_pointer>::pointer_to(*_M_local_buf);
204#else
205 return const_pointer(_M_local_buf);
206#endif
207 }
208
209 void
210 _M_capacity(size_type __capacity)
211 { _M_allocated_capacity = __capacity; }
212
213 void
214 _M_set_length(size_type __n)
215 {
216 _M_length(__n);
217 traits_type::assign(_M_data()[__n], _CharT());
218 }
219
220 bool
221 _M_is_local() const
222 { return _M_data() == _M_local_data(); }
223
224 // Create & Destroy
225 pointer
226 _M_create(size_type&, size_type);
227
228 void
229 _M_dispose()
230 {
231 if (!_M_is_local())
232 _M_destroy(_M_allocated_capacity);
233 }
234
235 void
236 _M_destroy(size_type __size) throw()
237 { _Alloc_traits::deallocate(_M_get_allocator(), _M_data(), __size + 1); }
238
239 // _M_construct_aux is used to implement the 21.3.1 para 15 which
240 // requires special behaviour if _InIterator is an integral type
241 template<typename _InIterator>
242 void
243 _M_construct_aux(_InIterator __beg, _InIterator __end,
244 std::__false_type)
245 {
246 typedef typename iterator_traits<_InIterator>::iterator_category _Tag;
247 _M_construct(__beg, __end, _Tag());
248 }
249
250 // _GLIBCXX_RESOLVE_LIB_DEFECTS
251 // 438. Ambiguity in the "do the right thing" clause
252 template<typename _Integer>
253 void
254 _M_construct_aux(_Integer __beg, _Integer __end, std::__true_type)
255 { _M_construct_aux_2(static_cast<size_type>(__beg), __end); }
256
257 void
258 _M_construct_aux_2(size_type __req, _CharT __c)
259 { _M_construct(__req, __c); }
260
261 template<typename _InIterator>
262 void
263 _M_construct(_InIterator __beg, _InIterator __end)
264 {
265 typedef typename std::__is_integer<_InIterator>::__type _Integral;
266 _M_construct_aux(__beg, __end, _Integral());
267 }
268
269 // For Input Iterators, used in istreambuf_iterators, etc.
270 template<typename _InIterator>
271 void
272 _M_construct(_InIterator __beg, _InIterator __end,
273 std::input_iterator_tag);
274
275 // For forward_iterators up to random_access_iterators, used for
276 // string::iterator, _CharT*, etc.
277 template<typename _FwdIterator>
278 void
279 _M_construct(_FwdIterator __beg, _FwdIterator __end,
280 std::forward_iterator_tag);
281
282 void
283 _M_construct(size_type __req, _CharT __c);
284
285 allocator_type&
286 _M_get_allocator()
287 { return _M_dataplus; }
288
289 const allocator_type&
290 _M_get_allocator() const
291 { return _M_dataplus; }

293 private:
294
295#ifdef _GLIBCXX_DISAMBIGUATE_REPLACE_INST
296 // The explicit instantiations in misc-inst.cc require this due to
297 // https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=64063
298 template<typename _Tp, bool _Requires =
299 !__are_same<_Tp, _CharT*>::__value
300 && !__are_same<_Tp, const _CharT*>::__value
301 && !__are_same<_Tp, iterator>::__value
302 && !__are_same<_Tp, const_iterator>::__value>
303 struct __enable_if_not_native_iterator
304 { typedef basic_string& __type; };
305 template<typename _Tp>
306 struct __enable_if_not_native_iterator<_Tp, false> { };
307#endif
308
309 size_type
310 _M_check(size_type __pos, const char* __s) const
311 {
312 if (__pos > this->size())
313 __throw_out_of_range_fmt(__N("%s: __pos (which is %zu) > "("%s: __pos (which is %zu) > " "this->size() (which is %zu)"
)
314 "this->size() (which is %zu)")("%s: __pos (which is %zu) > " "this->size() (which is %zu)"
),
315 __s, __pos, this->size());
316 return __pos;
317 }
318
319 void
320 _M_check_length(size_type __n1, size_type __n2, const char* __s) const
321 {
322 if (this->max_size() - (this->size() - __n1) < __n2)
323 __throw_length_error(__N(__s)(__s));
324 }
325
326
327 // NB: _M_limit doesn't check for a bad __pos value.
328 size_type
329 _M_limit(size_type __pos, size_type __off) const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
330 {
331 const bool __testoff = __off < this->size() - __pos;
332 return __testoff ? __off : this->size() - __pos;
333 }
334
335 // True if _Rep and source do not overlap.
336 bool
337 _M_disjunct(const _CharT* __s) const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
338 {
339 return (less<const _CharT*>()(__s, _M_data())
340 || less<const _CharT*>()(_M_data() + this->size(), __s));
341 }
342
343 // When __n = 1 way faster than the general multichar
344 // traits_type::copy/move/assign.
345 static void
346 _S_copy(_CharT* __d, const _CharT* __s, size_type __n)
347 {
348 if (__n == 1)
349 traits_type::assign(*__d, *__s);
350 else
351 traits_type::copy(__d, __s, __n);
352 }
353
354 static void
355 _S_move(_CharT* __d, const _CharT* __s, size_type __n)
356 {
357 if (__n == 1)
358 traits_type::assign(*__d, *__s);
359 else
360 traits_type::move(__d, __s, __n);
361 }
362
363 static void
364 _S_assign(_CharT* __d, size_type __n, _CharT __c)
365 {
366 if (__n == 1)
367 traits_type::assign(*__d, __c);
368 else
369 traits_type::assign(__d, __n, __c);
370 }
371
372 // _S_copy_chars is a separate template to permit specialization
373 // to optimize for the common case of pointers as iterators.
374 template<class _Iterator>
375 static void
376 _S_copy_chars(_CharT* __p, _Iterator __k1, _Iterator __k2)
377 {
378 for (; __k1 != __k2; ++__k1, (void)++__p)
379 traits_type::assign(*__p, *__k1); // These types are off.
380 }
381
382 static void
383 _S_copy_chars(_CharT* __p, iterator __k1, iterator __k2) _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
384 { _S_copy_chars(__p, __k1.base(), __k2.base()); }
385
386 static void
387 _S_copy_chars(_CharT* __p, const_iterator __k1, const_iterator __k2)
388 _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
389 { _S_copy_chars(__p, __k1.base(), __k2.base()); }
390
391 static void
392 _S_copy_chars(_CharT* __p, _CharT* __k1, _CharT* __k2) _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
393 { _S_copy(__p, __k1, __k2 - __k1); }
394
395 static void
396 _S_copy_chars(_CharT* __p, const _CharT* __k1, const _CharT* __k2)
397 _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
398 { _S_copy(__p, __k1, __k2 - __k1); }
399
400 static int
401 _S_compare(size_type __n1, size_type __n2) _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
402 {
403 const difference_type __d = difference_type(__n1 - __n2);
404
405 if (__d > __gnu_cxx::__numeric_traits<int>::__max)
406 return __gnu_cxx::__numeric_traits<int>::__max;
407 else if (__d < __gnu_cxx::__numeric_traits<int>::__min)
408 return __gnu_cxx::__numeric_traits<int>::__min;
409 else
410 return int(__d);
411 }

418 size_type __len2);

421 _M_erase(size_type __pos, size_type __n);

424 // Construct/copy/destroy:

428 /**
429 * @brief Default constructor creates an empty string.
430 */
431 basic_string()
432 _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPT_IF(is_nothrow_default_constructible<_Alloc>::value)noexcept(is_nothrow_default_constructible<_Alloc>::value
)
433 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data())
434 { _M_set_length(0); }

436 /**
437 * @brief Construct an empty string using allocator @a a.
438 */
439 explicit
440 basic_string(const _Alloc& __a) _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
441 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
442 { _M_set_length(0); }

444 /**
445 * @brief Construct string with copy of value of @a __str.
446 * @param __str Source string.
447 */
448 basic_string(const basic_string& __str)
449 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(),
450 _Alloc_traits::_S_select_on_copy(__str._M_get_allocator()))
451 { _M_construct(__str._M_data(), __str._M_data() + __str.length()); }
452
453 // _GLIBCXX_RESOLVE_LIB_DEFECTS
454 // 2583. no way to supply an allocator for basic_string(str, pos)
455 /**
456 * @brief Construct string as copy of a substring.
457 * @param __str Source string.
458 * @param __pos Index of first character to copy from.
459 * @param __a Allocator to use.
460 */
461 basic_string(const basic_string& __str, size_type __pos,
462 const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
463 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
464 {
465 const _CharT* __start = __str._M_data()
466 + __str._M_check(__pos, "basic_string::basic_string");
467 _M_construct(__start, __start + __str._M_limit(__pos, npos));
468 }
469
470 /**
471 * @brief Construct string as copy of a substring.
472 * @param __str Source string.
473 * @param __pos Index of first character to copy from.
474 * @param __n Number of characters to copy.
475 */
476 basic_string(const basic_string& __str, size_type __pos,
477 size_type __n)
478 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data())
479 {
480 const _CharT* __start = __str._M_data()
481 + __str._M_check(__pos, "basic_string::basic_string");
482 _M_construct(__start, __start + __str._M_limit(__pos, __n));
483 }
484
485 /**
486 * @brief Construct string as copy of a substring.
487 * @param __str Source string.
488 * @param __pos Index of first character to copy from.
489 * @param __n Number of characters to copy.
490 * @param __a Allocator to use.
491 */
492 basic_string(const basic_string& __str, size_type __pos,
493 size_type __n, const _Alloc& __a)
494 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
495 {
496 const _CharT* __start
497 = __str._M_data() + __str._M_check(__pos, "string::string");
498 _M_construct(__start, __start + __str._M_limit(__pos, __n));
499 }
500
501 /**
502 * @brief Construct string initialized by a character %array.
503 * @param __s Source character %array.
504 * @param __n Number of characters to copy.
505 * @param __a Allocator to use (default is default allocator).
506 *
507 * NB: @a __s must have at least @a __n characters, &apos;\\0&apos;
508 * has no special meaning.
509 */
510 basic_string(const _CharT* __s, size_type __n,
511 const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
512 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
513 { _M_construct(__s, __s + __n); }
514
515 /**
516 * @brief Construct string as copy of a C string.
517 * @param __s Source C string.
518 * @param __a Allocator to use (default is default allocator).
519 */
520#if __cpp_deduction_guides && ! defined _GLIBCXX_DEFINING_STRING_INSTANTIATIONS
521 // _GLIBCXX_RESOLVE_LIB_DEFECTS
522 // 3076. basic_string CTAD ambiguity
523 template<typename = _RequireAllocator<_Alloc>>
524#endif
525 basic_string(const _CharT* __s, const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
526 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
527 { _M_construct(__s, __s ? __s + traits_type::length(__s) : __s+npos); }
528
529 /**
530 * @brief Construct string as multiple characters.
531 * @param __n Number of characters.
532 * @param __c Character to use.
533 * @param __a Allocator to use (default is default allocator).
534 */
535#if __cpp_deduction_guides && ! defined _GLIBCXX_DEFINING_STRING_INSTANTIATIONS
536 // _GLIBCXX_RESOLVE_LIB_DEFECTS
537 // 3076. basic_string CTAD ambiguity
538 template<typename = _RequireAllocator<_Alloc>>
539#endif
540 basic_string(size_type __n, _CharT __c, const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
541 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
542 { _M_construct(__n, __c); }
543
544#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
545 /**
546 * @brief Move construct string.
547 * @param __str Source string.
548 *
549 * The newly-created string contains the exact contents of @a __str.
550 * @a __str is a valid, but unspecified string.
551 **/
552 basic_string(basic_string&& __str) noexcept
553 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), std::move(__str._M_get_allocator()))
554 {
555 if (__str._M_is_local())
556 {
557 traits_type::copy(_M_local_buf, __str._M_local_buf,
558 _S_local_capacity + 1);
559 }
560 else
561 {
562 _M_data(__str._M_data());
563 _M_capacity(__str._M_allocated_capacity);
564 }
565
566 // Must use _M_length() here not _M_set_length() because
567 // basic_stringbuf relies on writing into unallocated capacity so
568 // we mess up the contents if we put a '\0' in the string.
569 _M_length(__str.length());
570 __str._M_data(__str._M_local_data());
571 __str._M_set_length(0);
572 }
573
574 /**
575 * @brief Construct string from an initializer %list.
576 * @param __l std::initializer_list of characters.
577 * @param __a Allocator to use (default is default allocator).
578 */
579 basic_string(initializer_list<_CharT> __l, const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
580 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
581 { _M_construct(__l.begin(), __l.end()); }
582
583 basic_string(const basic_string& __str, const _Alloc& __a)
584 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
585 { _M_construct(__str.begin(), __str.end()); }
586
587 basic_string(basic_string&& __str, const _Alloc& __a)
588 noexcept(_Alloc_traits::_S_always_equal())
589 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
590 {
591 if (__str._M_is_local())
592 {
593 traits_type::copy(_M_local_buf, __str._M_local_buf,
594 _S_local_capacity + 1);
595 _M_length(__str.length());
596 __str._M_set_length(0);
597 }
598 else if (_Alloc_traits::_S_always_equal()
599 || __str.get_allocator() == __a)
600 {
601 _M_data(__str._M_data());
602 _M_length(__str.length());
603 _M_capacity(__str._M_allocated_capacity);
604 __str._M_data(__str._M_local_buf);
605 __str._M_set_length(0);
606 }
607 else
608 _M_construct(__str.begin(), __str.end());
609 }
610
611#endif // C++11
612
613 /**
614 * @brief Construct string as copy of a range.
615 * @param __beg Start of range.
616 * @param __end End of range.
617 * @param __a Allocator to use (default is default allocator).
618 */
619#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
620 template<typename _InputIterator,
621 typename = std::_RequireInputIter<_InputIterator>>
622#else
623 template<typename _InputIterator>
624#endif
625 basic_string(_InputIterator __beg, _InputIterator __end,
626 const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
627 : _M_dataplus(_M_local_data(), __a)
628 { _M_construct(__beg, __end); }
629
630#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201703L
631 /**
632 * @brief Construct string from a substring of a string_view.
633 * @param __t Source object convertible to string view.
634 * @param __pos The index of the first character to copy from __t.
635 * @param __n The number of characters to copy from __t.
636 * @param __a Allocator to use.
637 */
638 template<typename _Tp, typename = _If_sv<_Tp, void>>
639 basic_string(const _Tp& __t, size_type __pos, size_type __n,
640 const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
641 : basic_string(_S_to_string_view(__t).substr(__pos, __n), __a) { }
642
643 /**
644 * @brief Construct string from a string_view.
645 * @param __t Source object convertible to string view.
646 * @param __a Allocator to use (default is default allocator).
647 */
648 template<typename _Tp, typename = _If_sv<_Tp, void>>
649 explicit
650 basic_string(const _Tp& __t, const _Alloc& __a = _Alloc())
651 : basic_string(__sv_wrapper(_S_to_string_view(__t)), __a) { }
652#endif // C++17
653
654 /**
655 * @brief Destroy the string instance.
656 */
657 ~basic_string()
658 { _M_dispose(); }
659
660 /**
661 * @brief Assign the value of @a str to this string.
662 * @param __str Source string.
663 */
664 basic_string&
665 operator=(const basic_string& __str)
666 {
667#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
668 if (_Alloc_traits::_S_propagate_on_copy_assign())
669 {
670 if (!_Alloc_traits::_S_always_equal() && !_M_is_local()
671 && _M_get_allocator() != __str._M_get_allocator())
672 {
673 // Propagating allocator cannot free existing storage so must
674 // deallocate it before replacing current allocator.
675 if (__str.size() <= _S_local_capacity)
676 {
677 _M_destroy(_M_allocated_capacity);
678 _M_data(_M_local_data());
679 _M_set_length(0);
680 }
681 else
682 {
683 const auto __len = __str.size();
684 auto __alloc = __str._M_get_allocator();
685 // If this allocation throws there are no effects:
686 auto __ptr = _Alloc_traits::allocate(__alloc, __len + 1);
687 _M_destroy(_M_allocated_capacity);
688 _M_data(__ptr);
689 _M_capacity(__len);
690 _M_set_length(__len);
691 }
692 }
693 std::__alloc_on_copy(_M_get_allocator(), __str._M_get_allocator());
694 }
695#endif
696 return this->assign(__str);
697 }
698
699 /**
700 * @brief Copy contents of @a s into this string.
701 * @param __s Source null-terminated string.
702 */
703 basic_string&
704 operator=(const _CharT* __s)
705 { return this->assign(__s); }
706
707 /**
708 * @brief Set value to string of length 1.
709 * @param __c Source character.
710 *
711 * Assigning to a character makes this string length 1 and
712 * (*this)[0] == @a c.
713 */
714 basic_string&
715 operator=(_CharT __c)
716 {
717 this->assign(1, __c);
718 return *this;
719 }
720
721#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
722 /**
723 * @brief Move assign the value of @a str to this string.
724 * @param __str Source string.
725 *
726 * The contents of @a str are moved into this string (without copying).
727 * @a str is a valid, but unspecified string.
728 **/
729 // _GLIBCXX_RESOLVE_LIB_DEFECTS
730 // 2063. Contradictory requirements for string move assignment
731 basic_string&
732 operator=(basic_string&& __str)
733 noexcept(_Alloc_traits::_S_nothrow_move())
734 {
735 if (!_M_is_local() && _Alloc_traits::_S_propagate_on_move_assign()
736 && !_Alloc_traits::_S_always_equal()
737 && _M_get_allocator() != __str._M_get_allocator())
738 {
739 // Destroy existing storage before replacing allocator.
740 _M_destroy(_M_allocated_capacity);
741 _M_data(_M_local_data());
742 _M_set_length(0);
743 }
744 // Replace allocator if POCMA is true.
745 std::__alloc_on_move(_M_get_allocator(), __str._M_get_allocator());
746
747 if (__str._M_is_local())
748 {
749 // We've always got room for a short string, just copy it.
750 if (__str.size())
751 this->_S_copy(_M_data(), __str._M_data(), __str.size());
752 _M_set_length(__str.size());
753 }
754 else if (_Alloc_traits::_S_propagate_on_move_assign()
755 || _Alloc_traits::_S_always_equal()
756 || _M_get_allocator() == __str._M_get_allocator())
757 {
758 // Just move the allocated pointer, our allocator can free it.
759 pointer __data = nullptr;
760 size_type __capacity;
761 if (!_M_is_local())
762 {
763 if (_Alloc_traits::_S_always_equal())
764 {
765 // __str can reuse our existing storage.
766 __data = _M_data();
767 __capacity = _M_allocated_capacity;
768 }
769 else // __str can't use it, so free it.
770 _M_destroy(_M_allocated_capacity);
771 }
772
773 _M_data(__str._M_data());
774 _M_length(__str.length());
775 _M_capacity(__str._M_allocated_capacity);
776 if (__data)
777 {
778 __str._M_data(__data);
779 __str._M_capacity(__capacity);
780 }
781 else
782 __str._M_data(__str._M_local_buf);
783 }
784 else // Need to do a deep copy
785 assign(__str);
786 __str.clear();
787 return *this;
788 }
789
790 /**
791 * @brief Set value to string constructed from initializer %list.
792 * @param __l std::initializer_list.
793 */
794 basic_string&
795 operator=(initializer_list<_CharT> __l)
796 {
797 this->assign(__l.begin(), __l.size());
798 return *this;
799 }
800#endif // C++11
801
802#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201703L
803 /**
804 * @brief Set value to string constructed from a string_view.
805 * @param __svt An object convertible to string_view.
806 */
807 template<typename _Tp>
808 _If_sv<_Tp, basic_string&>
809 operator=(const _Tp& __svt)
810 { return this->assign(__svt); }
811
812 /**
813 * @brief Convert to a string_view.
814 * @return A string_view.
815 */
816 operator __sv_type() const noexcept
817 { return __sv_type(data(), size()); }
818#endif // C++17

820 // Iterators:
821 /**
822 * Returns a read/write iterator that points to the first character in
823 * the %string.
824 */
825 iterator
826 begin() _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
827 { return iterator(_M_data()); }
828
829 /**
830 * Returns a read-only (constant) iterator that points to the first
831 * character in the %string.
832 */
833 const_iterator
834 begin() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
835 { return const_iterator(_M_data()); }
836
837 /**
838 * Returns a read/write iterator that points one past the last
839 * character in the %string.
840 */
841 iterator
842 end() _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
843 { return iterator(_M_data() + this->size()); }
844
845 /**
846 * Returns a read-only (constant) iterator that points one past the
847 * last character in the %string.
848 */
849 const_iterator
850 end() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
851 { return const_iterator(_M_data() + this->size()); }
852
853 /**
854 * Returns a read/write reverse iterator that points to the last
855 * character in the %string. Iteration is done in reverse element
856 * order.
857 */
858 reverse_iterator
859 rbegin() _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
860 { return reverse_iterator(this->end()); }
861
862 /**
863 * Returns a read-only (constant) reverse iterator that points
864 * to the last character in the %string. Iteration is done in
865 * reverse element order.
866 */
867 const_reverse_iterator
868 rbegin() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
869 { return const_reverse_iterator(this->end()); }
870
871 /**
872 * Returns a read/write reverse iterator that points to one before the
873 * first character in the %string. Iteration is done in reverse
874 * element order.
875 */
876 reverse_iterator
877 rend() _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
878 { return reverse_iterator(this->begin()); }
879
880 /**
881 * Returns a read-only (constant) reverse iterator that points
882 * to one before the first character in the %string. Iteration
883 * is done in reverse element order.
884 */
885 const_reverse_iterator
886 rend() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
887 { return const_reverse_iterator(this->begin()); }
888
889#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
890 /**
891 * Returns a read-only (constant) iterator that points to the first
892 * character in the %string.
893 */
894 const_iterator
895 cbegin() const noexcept
896 { return const_iterator(this->_M_data()); }
897
898 /**
899 * Returns a read-only (constant) iterator that points one past the
900 * last character in the %string.
901 */
902 const_iterator
903 cend() const noexcept
904 { return const_iterator(this->_M_data() + this->size()); }
905
906 /**
907 * Returns a read-only (constant) reverse iterator that points
908 * to the last character in the %string. Iteration is done in
909 * reverse element order.
910 */
911 const_reverse_iterator
912 crbegin() const noexcept
913 { return const_reverse_iterator(this->end()); }
914
915 /**
916 * Returns a read-only (constant) reverse iterator that points
917 * to one before the first character in the %string. Iteration
918 * is done in reverse element order.
919 */
920 const_reverse_iterator
921 crend() const noexcept
922 { return const_reverse_iterator(this->begin()); }
923#endif
924
925 public:
926 // Capacity:
927 /// Returns the number of characters in the string, not including any
928 /// null-termination.
929 size_type
930 size() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
931 { return _M_string_length; }
932
933 /// Returns the number of characters in the string, not including any
934 /// null-termination.
935 size_type
936 length() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
937 { return _M_string_length; }
938
939 /// Returns the size() of the largest possible %string.
940 size_type
941 max_size() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
942 { return (_Alloc_traits::max_size(_M_get_allocator()) - 1) / 2; }
943
944 /**
945 * @brief Resizes the %string to the specified number of characters.
946 * @param __n Number of characters the %string should contain.
947 * @param __c Character to fill any new elements.
948 *
949 * This function will %resize the %string to the specified
950 * number of characters. If the number is smaller than the
951 * %string's current size the %string is truncated, otherwise
952 * the %string is extended and new elements are %set to @a __c.
953 */
954 void
955 resize(size_type __n, _CharT __c);
956
957 /**
958 * @brief Resizes the %string to the specified number of characters.
959 * @param __n Number of characters the %string should contain.
960 *
961 * This function will resize the %string to the specified length. If
962 * the new size is smaller than the %string's current size the %string
963 * is truncated, otherwise the %string is extended and new characters
964 * are default-constructed. For basic types such as char, this means
965 * setting them to 0.
966 */
967 void
968 resize(size_type __n)
969 { this->resize(__n, _CharT()); }
970
971#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
972 /// A non-binding request to reduce capacity() to size().
973 void
974 shrink_to_fit() noexcept
975 {
976#if __cpp_exceptions199711L
977 if (capacity() > size())
978 {
979 try
980 { reserve(0); }
981 catch(...)
982 { }
983 }
984#endif
985 }
986#endif
987
988 /**
989 * Returns the total number of characters that the %string can hold
990 * before needing to allocate more memory.
991 */
992 size_type
993 capacity() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
994 {
995 return _M_is_local() ? size_type(_S_local_capacity)
996 : _M_allocated_capacity;
997 }
998
999 /**
1000 * @brief Attempt to preallocate enough memory for specified number of
1001 * characters.
1002 * @param __res_arg Number of characters required.
1003 * @throw std::length_error If @a __res_arg exceeds @c max_size().
1004 *
1005 * This function attempts to reserve enough memory for the
1006 * %string to hold the specified number of characters. If the
1007 * number requested is more than max_size(), length_error is
1008 * thrown.
1009 *
1010 * The advantage of this function is that if optimal code is a
1011 * necessity and the user can determine the string length that will be
1012 * required, the user can reserve the memory in %advance, and thus
1013 * prevent a possible reallocation of memory and copying of %string
1014 * data.
1015 */
1016 void
1017 reserve(size_type __res_arg = 0);
1018
1019 /**
1020 * Erases the string, making it empty.
1021 */
1022 void
1023 clear() _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
1024 { _M_set_length(0); }
1025
1026 /**
1027 * Returns true if the %string is empty. Equivalent to
1028 * <code>*this == ""</code>.
1029 */
1030 _GLIBCXX_NODISCARD bool
1031 empty() const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
1032 { return this->size() == 0; }
1033
1034 // Element access:
1035 /**
1036 * @brief Subscript access to the data contained in the %string.
1037 * @param __pos The index of the character to access.
1038 * @return Read-only (constant) reference to the character.
1039 *
1040 * This operator allows for easy, array-style, data access.
1041 * Note that data access with this operator is unchecked and
1042 * out_of_range lookups are not defined. (For checked lookups
1043 * see at().)
1044 */
1045 const_reference
1046 operator[] (size_type __pos) const _GLIBCXX_NOEXCEPTnoexcept
1047 {
1048 __glibcxx_assert(__pos <= size());
1049 return _M_data()[__pos];
1050 }
1051
1052 /**
1053 * @brief Subscript access to the data contained in the %string.
1054 * @param __pos The index of the character to access.
1055 * @return Read/write reference to the character.
1056 *
1057 * This operator allows for easy, array-style, data access.
1058 * Note that data access with this operator is unchecked and
1059 * out_of_range lookups are not defined. (For checked lookups
1060 * see at().)
1061 */
1062 reference
1063 operator[](size_type __pos)
1064 {
1065 // Allow pos == size() both in C++98 mode, as v3 extension,
1066 // and in C++11 mode.
1067 __glibcxx_assert(__pos <= size());
1068 // In pedantic mode be strict in C++98 mode.
1069 _GLIBCXX_DEBUG_PEDASSERT(__cplusplus >= 201103L || __pos < size());
1070 return _M_data()[__pos];
1071 }
1072
1073 /**
1074 * @brief Provides access to the data contained in the %string.
1075 * @param __n The index of the character to access.
1076 * @return Read-only (const) reference to the character.
1077 * @throw std::out_of_range If @a n is an invalid index.
1078 *
1079 * This function provides for safer data access. The parameter is
1080 * first checked that it is in the range of the string. The function
1081 * throws out_of_range if the check fails.
1082 */
1083 const_reference
1084 at(size_type __n) const
1085 {
1086 if (__n >= this->size())
1087 __throw_out_of_range_fmt(__N("basic_string::at: __n "("basic_string::at: __n " "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "
"(which is %zu)")
1088 "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "("basic_string::at: __n " "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "
"(which is %zu)")
1089 "(which is %zu)")("basic_string::at: __n " "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "
"(which is %zu)"),
1090 __n, this->size());
1091 return _M_data()[__n];
1092 }
1093
1094 /**
1095 * @brief Provides access to the data contained in the %string.
1096 * @param __n The index of the character to access.
1097 * @return Read/write reference to the character.
1098 * @throw std::out_of_range If @a n is an invalid index.
1099 *
1100 * This function provides for safer data access. The parameter is
1101 * first checked that it is in the range of the string. The function
1102 * throws out_of_range if the check fails.
1103 */
1104 reference
1105 at(size_type __n)
1106 {
1107 if (__n >= size())
1108 __throw_out_of_range_fmt(__N("basic_string::at: __n "("basic_string::at: __n " "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "
"(which is %zu)")
1109 "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "("basic_string::at: __n " "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "
"(which is %zu)")
1110 "(which is %zu)")("basic_string::at: __n " "(which is %zu) >= this->size() "
"(which is %zu)"),
1111 __n, this->size());
1112 return _M_data()[__n];
1113 }
1114
1115#if __cplusplus201103L >= 201103L
1116 /**
1117 * Returns a read/write reference to the data at the first
1118 * element of the %string.
1119 */
1120 reference
1121 front() noexcept
1122 {
1123 __glibcxx_assert(!empty());
1124 return operator[](0);
1125 }
1126

1128 * Returns a read-only (constant) reference to the data at the first
1129 * element of the %string.
1130 */
1131 const_reference
1132 front() const noexcept
1133 {
1134 __glibcxx_assert(!empty());
1135 return operator[](0);
1136 }
1137
1138 /**
1139 * Returns a read/write reference to the data at the last
1140 * element of the %string.
1141 */
1142 reference
1143 back() noexcept
1144 {
1145 __glibcxx_assert(!empty());
1146 return operator[](this->size() - 1);
1147 }
1148
1149 /**
1150 * Returns a read-only (constant) reference to the data at the
1151 * last element of the %string.
1152 */
1153 const_reference
1154 back() const noexcept
1155 {
1156 __glibcxx_assert(!empty());
1157 return operator[](this->size() - 1);

1159#endif

1169 { return this->append(__str); }

1178 { return this->append(__s); }

1180 /**
1181 * @brief Append a character.
1182 * @param __c The character to append.
1183 * @return Reference to this string.
1184 */
1185 basic_string&
1186 operator+=(_CharT __c)
1187 {
1188 this->push_back(__c);
1189 return *this;
1190 }

1217 * @param __str The string to append.

1222 { return _M_append(__str._M_data(), __str.size()); }
